article.headline: Stetson 52, North Florida 40
article.story: DELAND, Fla. (AP) -- Senior guard Anthony Register scored 15 points as Stetson snapped the nation's longest losing streak in NCAA Division I with a 52-40 victory over North Florida Monday. Stetson had lost its last 15 games, including the first 10 of the 2005-06 season, before beating North Florida. The Ospreys fell to 3-7 overall and 0-3 in the Atlantic Sun Conference. The Hatters are now 1-2 in A-Sun play. Register scored 10 of his 15 points in the first half as Stetson led 27-12 at halftime. The Hatters established a new modern-day team record for fewest points allowed in a half. The old record of 13 points was reached three times, the last against North Carolina State on Nov. 26, 2000. Senior guard E.J. Gordon added 14 points and seven rebounds for Stetson, while senior forward Karl Hollingsworth chipped in 10 points and eight rebounds. Junior forward Rashad Williams scored 12 points and grabbed 11 rebounds to lead North Florida. The Ospreys played without leading scorer and rebounder Alain Laroche. The senior forward missed his second straight game because of an injured right wrist. North Florida trailed 27-12 at the half but cut the margin to five points, 33-28, with a 16-5 run. However, Gordon sandwiched short jumpers around a baseline jumper by Register to get the Hatters' lead to 39-28 with 9:37 left.
